					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10930588#post-4205514</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10930588/scp-4360#post-4205514</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 02 Apr 2019 15:22:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Nice thing that does a thing. +1</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Testing of SCP-4360 may only be done using Foundation-approved DVDs.</p> </blockquote> <p>&quot;Foundation-approved&quot; seems redundant, just say &quot;approved&quot;.</p> <blockquote> <p>despite no obvious source of power.</p> </blockquote> <p>It's a tree. Why can't its photosynthesis be the source of power?</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-4360's Object Class is pending an upgrade to Euclid-Class.</p> </blockquote> <p>Not a proper noun. Should just be &quot;SCP-4630's object class&quot;.<br /> Also if you're already talking about classes, you can just say Euclid.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
